quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  88,1,"Has there come to you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>the news of the Overwhelming<i class=""s"">(event) </i>{1}?",footnotes:1:The Day of Judgment.
  88,2,"Some faces on that day are<i class=""s"">(subdued) </i>in reverence,"
  88,3,"toiling, exhausted,"
  88,4,"<span class="h">roasting{1}</span>in a hot fire,",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Abu ‘Amr, Shu’ba and Ya’qub read it as: “…made to roast in a hot fire,”</span>
  88,5,"given to drink from a boiling spring."
  88,6,"They have no food except of a thorny bush"
  88,7,"which neither nourishes nor satisfies hunger."
  88,8,"Some faces on that day are blissful,"
  88,9,"well pleased with their endeavor,"
  88,10,"in a lofty Garden:"
